summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed of gift from the J. M. Colman Company, a corporation, to The City of Seattle, dated the 21st day of March, 1910, to The Tract designated as "Park Tract A" in the Plat of "Colman's First Addition to the City of Seattle", as the same is platted and of record on page 86 of Volume 18 of plats in the records of King County, State of Washington.
